designs  w engine  c galibier  production cars  veyron   chiron  citations  references  see also  external links historyedit at the urging of thenchairman ferdinand piëch volkswagen purchased the rights to produce cars under the bugatti marque in june  this followed the earlier volkswagen purchases of the lamborghini marque by vws audi subsidiary the rollsroyce factory in crewe united kingdom and the bentley marque on  december  volkswagen officially incorporated bugatti automobiles sas with former vw drivetrain chief karlheinz neumann as president the company purchased the  château saint jean formerly ettore bugattis guest house in dorlisheim near molsheim and began refurbishing it to serve as the companys headquarters the original factory was still in the hands of snecma who were unwilling to part with it at the pebble beach concours delegance in august  vw announced that they would instead build a new modern atelier factory next to and south of the château the atelier was officially inaugurated on  september  bugatti automobiles sas is a wholly owned subsidiary of the volkswagen ag  after the veyrons discontinuation in  the new bugatti model was revealed to be the chiron in  with an liter w engine delivering  horse power and an electronically limited top speed of  miles per hour and a price of about € the chiron attempts to vastly surpass the veyrons performance concept carsedit italdesign giugiaro designsedit volkswagen commissioned italdesigns giorgetto giugiaro to design a series of concept cars to return the marque to prominence the first example the eb  was a twodoor coupé and was introduced at the paris motor show in  it was followed by the fourdoor eb  touring sedan introduced at the geneva motor show in  later that year the  chiron was shown at the iaa in frankfurt volkswagen designsedit volkswagen designed the final bugatti concept the eb  gt in house bugatti introduced the eb  at the  tokyo motor show w engineedit all of these early concepts featured a  ps  kw  hp cylinder engine this was the firstever wconfiguration engine on a passenger vehicle with three blocks of  cylinders each it shared many components with volkswagens modular engine family c galibieredit main article bugatti c galibier the c galibier was first unveiled during celebration of the centenary of the marque in molsheim the presentation was only for bugatti customers the car show in molsheim showed the car in blue carbon fibre and aluminum parts one year later bugatti showed the world the c galibier concept at vw group night at the geneva auto show in a new black and aluminum color combination the galibier a  hp sedan was first shown as a concept in  and when they planned to put it into production in  it would have cost about  million it would use the same cylinder litre engine as the veyron but instead of four turbos the c galibier would instead use two superchargers to deliver better torque production would require new facilities in molsheim france to be refitted which pushed back potential deliveries until  in  it was announced that the car will never be produced as they wish to focus on a veyron replacement production carsedit bugatti eb gt in the s the bugatti brand was brought back as bugatti automobili spa in italy the company produced the eb in the s which put bugatti back on the modern supercar scene the company was then bought by vw at the end of the th century veyron edit main article bugatti veyron veyron  development of this vehicle began with the  eb  veyron concept car which itself had a chassis based on that of the bugatti  chiron concept car it was similar in design and appearance to the final veyron production car one major difference was the eb s use of a w engine with three banks of six cylinders the veyrons chief designer was hartmut warkuss and the exterior was designed by jozef kabaň of volkswagen rather than giorgetto giugiaro of italdesign who had handled the three prior bugatti concepts the then – volkswagen group chairman ferdinand piëch announced the veyron at the  geneva motor show it was promised to be the fastest most powerful and most expensive car in history instead of the w it would use a vrwrstyle w engine first seen in the  bentley hunaudières concept car the w would have four turbochargers and produce a quoted metric  horsepower see engine section for details on the power output top speed was promised at  kmh  mph and the price was announced at € million development continued throughout  and the eb  veyron was promoted to advanced concept status in late  bugatti announced that the car officially called the bugatti veyron  would go into production in  piëch retired that year as chairman of the volkswagen group and was replaced by bernd pischetsrieder the new chairman promptly sent the veyron back to the drawing board for major revisions neumann was replaced as bugatti president by thomas bscher in december  and substantial modifications were made to the veyron under the guidance of a former vw engineer bugatti engineering chief wolfgang schreiber the veyron costs € net price without taxescitation needed prices vary by exchange rates and local taxes like value added taxes prices for the uk or the us are over £ or around  it was noted in an april issue of live magazine weekly mens magazine with the sunday times that customers are free to order additional extras which can push the price up by the cost of a rolls royce phantom during an episode of top gear the car was compared to the concorde as a feat of technology chironedit at the  geneva auto show bugatti premiered the bugatti chiron as a successor to the veyron  the pricing is set at  million euros the car is expected to have  horsepower and will be capped at  kmh  mph for road use it can accelerate from  kmh in  seconds production is limited to  units unlike the veyron the chiron is expected to make a profit citationsedit  a b c volkswagen ag  p   a b c volkswagen ag  p   a b c volkswagen ag  p   cremer   bbc   bugatti c